    <p>By some twists of fate, I suddenly found myself at the airport, saying goodbye to a friend returning to their home country.</p>
    <p>When I was a child, watching TV made me think that buying a ticket to cross the Eurasian continent with just a phone call was a cool thing. It was like seeing older sisters working on laptops on planes or trains; it made me feel that one day I would be like that, very cool.</p>
