    <p>The sudden message made my head swell but also left me incredibly stable and calm. Tears were like water just filled in a kettle; one shake and they would overflow. I could only walk forward, perfectly balanced.</p>
    <p>And all these feelings might just be similar fragments of life memories I once had, only back then, I was young and in my hometown. Now, I am far away, thousands of miles across a 12-hour flight. In this country where I have stayed for many years, through various adventures in life, I seem to have been to many places, far more than in China. I have taken a 9-hour train ride to the northernmost tip of this continent (or small island); I have taken a boat for over an hour to hike and watch birds on a deserted island. I might even leave a quarter of my life in this place, maybe more. It went so far that when I landed in Manchester from New York, the moment I landed, it felt like I had returned home.</p>
